Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

- Total Revenue = $5,755,241.17

Gross Profit Margin = ($1,075,241.17 / $5,755,241.17) × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 0.1868 × 100%
Gross Profit Margin = 18.68%

## Step 2: Calculate the Operating Cash Flow Ratio
Operating Cash Flow Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities

From the cash flow statement:
- Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = -$7,724,112.71

From the balance sheet:
- Total Current Liabilities (End amount) = $737,762.05

Operating Cash Flow Ratio = -$7,724,112.71 / $737,762.05
